FBIS4-52174 "dreas089_i_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-089 Daily Report 5 May 1994 Cambodia Reports on King's Proposed Peace Talks Continue Reports on King's Proposed Peace Talks Continue CPP Supports King's Proposal BK0505151794 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1300 GMT 5 May 94 BK0505151794 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1300 GMT 5 May 94 Cambodian BFN ["Message from the Cambodian People's Party to His Majesty the King"; issued in Phnom Penh on 3 May -- read by announcer] [Text] Respectfully to His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk Varaman, king of the Kingdom of Cambodia. Your Majesty: We, your children in the Cambodian People's Party [CPP], would like to beg permission to express our support for Your Majesty's clear-sighted idea on an unconditional, immediate, complete, and static cease-fire as a step toward achieving national reconciliation, ending the war of bloodshed, and bringing peace and security to the Cambodian motherland and people. For the cause of the Cambodian nation, motherland, and people, we will always follow Your Majesty's lofty idea. Please, Your Majesty, accept our loftiest salutations. Please forgive any impropriaties. [Signed] Chea Sim, chairman of the CPP [Dated] Phnom Penh, 3 May
